# Esiana Product Identity

Esiana is **campaign narrative infrastructure**, not a VTT. Source: [philosophy.md](../../philosophy.md).

## Focus on

- Continuity, historical state, collaborative worldbuilding
- Knowledge revelation and player discovery (not omniscient exposure)
- Long-term campaign memory and interconnected lore
- Extensible systems over hardcoded assumptions

## Design priorities (in order)

1. Narrative continuity over combat tooling
2. Knowledge organization over rules execution
3. Temporal world state over static wiki pages
4. Player discovery over omniscient data exposure

## Anti-goals — push back or scope as plugin only

Do not build toward: tactical combat simulators, Foundry replacement, rules automation engines, virtual tabletops, character optimization platforms, live-service MMO campaign hosts, initiative/LOS/combat automation.

Maps are **world-history views** (temporal projection, lore pins), not tactical battle simulators.

## UX tone

Calm, restrained, lore-forward. Avoid startup-dashboard chaos and over-decorated fantasy chrome. Experience direction: [design-philosophy.md](../../design-philosophy.md).

Reject **Dashboard** in user-facing copy — use **Campaign Home**. TTRPG clarity over literary abstraction (GM, Game Master, Writer stay; Steward does not replace GM in UI).

## Feature gate

Before adding a feature, ask: Does it strengthen narrative continuity, discovery, or temporal world state?

If it primarily automates combat or replaces a VTT, decline or scope as an optional plugin only.
